2. build and polish their technique in art, thus develop a professional attitude;
3. understand issues of Chinese art and develop individual reflections; and

4. develop and broaden their critical thinking skills through different perspectives through the system of visiting artists/ critics

After completing the course, students will be able to:

- identify their research direction, and provide guidance on conceptual development;
- monitor their progress of research and polish their concepts;
- understand their strength and weakness, thus to develop necessary skill to cope with their objectives in their graduation work; and

- polish their presentation skills, in order to achieve a better result despite various constrains.

